caption: Ordered through grubhub and sent a lot on panda only to get the wrong order. I called up to panda and they said i can come pick up the correction. I told them no thats why i paid for delivery. They tried to tell me there was nothing they could do. I told them they can put the missing items in through grubhub and pay for the delivery. They said okay. 45 minutes went by nothing. Called again spoke to 3 people about the issue. One said we will bring the food. The food came and i took like 3 bites and stomach started to hurt. Then i couldnt keep anything down for a day or 2. Im pretry sure they did something to my food. Never again!  POOR SERVICE!

I literally stood in the lobby for 20 minutes with no acknowledgement. They were so busy trying to make drive thru orders they just ignored that I was even standing there. Worst service out of all the Panda’s I’ve been to. Woulda been easier to sit in the drive thru for 20 minutes. At least then I would have gotten my order taken.

This is a great Panda store.  I brought my dad here for the first and he loved it.  The staff was very friendly and the food was fresh and delicious.  We were even there at a weird time about 2 PM so basically in between meals, but everything was still excellent.  We even had enough orange chicken and teriyaki chicken, and rice left that we took some home for my mom and she also loved it.  We got 3 meals for about 20 bucks and we got sodas while at the store if we would have have had waters, the food would have only been like 15-16 bucks and plenty to feed three people.  Great deal and a great store.

My first experience with Panda Express: it was lunchtime and the line was long - no problem. I didnt realize it was kind of like the Subway of Chinese food(I want this and this ...). Choices were vast and they will give samples which is nice, but slows things down a bit. We ordered white rice, mixed vegetables, teriyaki chicken, and broccoli beef. Biggest issue- ALL of the food was barely warm. At lunch that food should have been steaming. This was very disappointing because it was tasty. I may try it 1 more time in my area for comparison.

Utterly Incomprehensible!  My wife visits Panda Express this evening and orders fried rice and a veggie spring roll (as she is a vegetarian).   She takes a bite of the spring roll and while chewing realizes something is off.....they gave her a pork egg roll.  She immediately spits it out and goes back to the counter giving Panda Express the benefit of the doubt thinking they may have just mixed it up and has the person at the counter reply "yea, we gave you a pork egg roll because we were all out of the veggie spring rolls".  WHAT?  You have no idea if that customer is allergic to pork, has a religious reason for not eating pork, or anything else, but you just decide to give them a pork egg roll as a substitution and on top of that don't even bother MENTIONING that fact?  To say this was massively careless would be an understatement!!
